main event: An elongated fireball was observed over Keesler AFB, Mississippi, on April 29, 1967.
interesting points: The observation lasted for about 2 minutes,The object moved in a westerly direction,There were no photographs or physical evidence collected,The report speculated the object was an astro phenomenon, possibly a meteor,The witness experienced a clear and calm night without a moon.
witness description: standing in neighbor's yard looking up
